<title>ITALY: Italy's Perugia sees August CPI at 3.5 pct yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Italy's Perugia sees August CPI at 3.5 pct yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>PERUGIA, Italy 1996-08-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian city of Perugia said its August consumer price index rose 0.1 percent month-on-month and 3.5 percent year-on-year.</p>
<p>In July, Perugia's inflation rate fell 0.4 percent but rose 3.5 percent respectively.</p>
<p>Perugia is one of 10 Italian cities publishing inflation data yesterday and today.</p>
<p>The city's CPI has a weighting of 1.26 percent on the national index. The 10 sample cities have a combined weighting of 69.67 percent on the total index.  </p>
<p>Following is the breakdown of the price changes.</p>
<p>(figures in brackets refer to July 1996):</p>
<p>					    Month/Month     Year/Year</p>
<p>    General index		     0.1   (-0.4)    3.5  (3.5)</p>
<p>    Food				  0.2   (-0.2)    4.9  (4.6)</p>
<p>    Clothing and footwear	   0.0    (0.2)    4.4  (4.4)</p>
<p>    Housing and utility charges   0.6   (-2.8)    4.3  (3.7)</p>
<p>    Furniture			   0.1    (0.0)    3.2  (4.3)</p>
<p>    Health services		   0.0   (-0.3)    2.3  (2.3)</p>
<p>    Transportation		    0.3    (0.2)    4.1  (4.3)</p>
<p>    Entertainment and culture     0.0   (-1.9)    1.3  (0.4)</p>
<p>    Education			   0.2    (0.3)    4.8  (6.1)</p>
<p>    Hotels and restaurants	  0.0    (0.0)    2.8  (2.8)</p>
<p>    Other goods or services	-0.3   (-0.1)    1.8  (2.0)</p>
<p>-- Milan newsroom ++392 66129526</p>
